---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Creating Projects">
  <h2>Creating Projects</h2>
  <p>
    Rep-li-bot uses a structured builder flow to help you create apps
    without writing any code.
  </p>

  <h3>The Builder Flow</h3>

  <h4>1. Launcher Screen</h4>
  <p>
    The launcher shows your existing projects. From here you can:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Open an existing project</li>
    <li>Create a new project</li>
    <li>Delete or duplicate projects</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>2. Builder Brief</h4>
  <p>
    When creating a new project, enter a clear description of what you want.
    The more specific you are, the better the results.
  </p>
  <pre><code>Example: "A habit tracker that helps me build daily routines.
I want to:
- Set habits with name and frequency (daily/weekly)
- Check off habits as I complete them
- See a streak counter for consecutive days
- View weekly progress on a simple chart"</code></pre>

  <h4>3. Generation Process</h4>
  <p>
    When you click "Generate", Rep-li-bot:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Sends your description to the AI provider</li>
    <li>Validates the generated code for safety and correctness</li>
    <li>Performs one repair pass if issues are detected</li>
    <li>Records generation metadata (attempts, warnings, notes)</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>4. Preview Mode</h4>
  <p>
    Preview your app in a sandboxed iframe. This allows you to test
    functionality before running as a standalone app.
  </p>

  <h4>5. Run Mode</h4>
  <p>
    When satisfied with the preview, click "Run" to launch your app
    in its own window.
  </p>

  <h3>Managing Projects</h3>
  <p>
    Projects are stored locally in your workspace. Each project contains:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>project.json</code> - Project metadata and configuration</li>
    <li><code>src/</code> - Generated source code</li>
    <li><code>assets/</code> - Project resources</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Best Practices</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Start simple and iterate</li>
    <li>Be specific about user interactions</li>
    <li>Mention data types and structures explicitly</li>
    <li>Test in preview mode before running</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
